Example of Denoising (db4, periodization, soft)¶

In [16]:
# Function to perform wavelet denoising
def wavelet_denoise(data, wavelet, level):
    # Decompose to get the wavelet coefficients
    coeff = pywt.wavedec(data, wavelet, mode="per", level=level)
    sigma = (1/0.6745) * mad(coeff[-level])
    
    # Threshold for each detail coefficient
    uthresh = sigma * np.sqrt(2*np.log(len(data)))
    coeff[1:] = (pywt.threshold(i, value=uthresh, mode='soft') for i in coeff[1:])
    
    # Reconstruct the signal using the thresholded coefficients
    return pywt.waverec(coeff, wavelet, mode='per')

# Median Absolute Deviation: a robust measure of variability
def mad(data):
    return np.median(np.abs(data - np.median(data)))

# Perform denoising
eog_data_dn = wavelet_denoise(eog_data, 'db4', level=4)

# 그래프 그리기
# 임의의 10초 구간 선택 (예: 100초부터 110초까지)
start_sec = 4645 #4620 N2
end_sec = 4650 # 4650 R
start_index = int(start_sec * sfreq)
end_index = int(end_sec * sfreq)

time_intvl = times[start_index:end_index]

selected_eog_data = eog_data[start_index:end_index]
selected_eog_data_dn = eog_data_dn[start_index:end_index]

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))
plt.plot(time_intvl, selected_eog_data, label='original', color='black', alpha=0.5)
plt.plot(time_intvl, selected_eog_data_dn, label='denoised', color='red')
plt.xlabel("Time (seconds)")
plt.ylabel("uV")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Function to perform wavelet denoising
def wavelet_denoise(data, wavelet, level):
    # Decompose to get the wavelet coefficients
    coeff = pywt.wavedec(data, wavelet, mode="per", level=level)
    sigma = (1/0.6745) * mad(coeff[-level])
    
    # Threshold for each detail coefficient
    uthresh = sigma * np.sqrt(2*np.log(len(data)))
    coeff[:] = (pywt.threshold(i, value=uthresh*10, mode='greater') for i in coeff[:])
    
    # Reconstruct the signal using the thresholded coefficients
    return pywt.waverec(coeff, wavelet, mode='per')

# Median Absolute Deviation: a robust measure of variability
def mad(data):
    return np.median(np.abs(data - np.median(data)))

# Perform denoising
eog_data_fs = wavelet_denoise(eog_data, 'db4', level=3)

import matplotlib.patches as mpatches

def plot_eog_with_annotations(raw, start_sec, end_sec, sfreq, eog_data, eog_data_dn):
    # Calculate start and end indices
    start_index = int(start_sec * sfreq)
    end_index = int(end_sec * sfreq)

    # Time interval
    time_intvl = np.arange(start_index, end_index) / sfreq

    # Select EOG data within the time range
    selected_eog_data = eog_data[start_index:end_index]
    selected_eog_data_fs= eog_data_fs[start_index:end_index]

    # Prepare to plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

    # Plot EOG data
    ax1 = plt.subplot(2, 1, 1)  # Top subplot for the EOG data
    ax1.plot(time_intvl, selected_eog_data, label='Original', color='black', alpha=0.5)
    ax1.plot(time_intvl, selected_eog_data_fs, label='Denoised', color='red')
    ax1.set_xlabel("Time (seconds)")
    ax1.set_ylabel("uV")
    ax1.legend()

    # Prepare annotations plot
    ax2 = plt.subplot(2, 1, 2)  # Bottom subplot for the annotations

    # Slice the raw data to focus on the desired time interval
    raw_sliced = raw.copy().crop(tmin=start_sec, tmax=end_sec)
    annotations = raw_sliced.annotations

    # Unique annotations and their corresponding colors
    unique_descriptions = np.unique(annotations.description)
    color_map = plt.cm.get_cmap('tab20', len(unique_descriptions))
    color_dict = {desc: color_map(i) for i, desc in enumerate(unique_descriptions)}

    # Create legend handles
    legend_handles = []

    # Plot each annotation as a colored segment
    for onset, duration, description in zip(annotations.onset, annotations.duration, annotations.description):
        onset_time = onset - start_sec  # adjust onset to local time interval
        if onset_time >= 0:
            line = ax2.plot([onset_time, onset_time + duration], [1, 1], color=color_dict[description], linewidth=10)
            # Add to legend handles if not already there
            if description not in [handle.get_label() for handle in legend_handles]:
                legend_handles.append(mpatches.Patch(color=color_dict[description], label=description))

    # Hide y-axis and spines for annotation plot
    ax2.yaxis.set_visible(False)
    ax2.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    ax2.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    ax2.spines['left'].set_visible(False)
    ax2.set_xlabel("Time (seconds)")

    # Add legend for annotations
    ax2.legend(handles=legend_handles, loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(0.5, -0.1), ncol=3)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Function to perform wavelet denoising
def wavelet_denoise(data, wavelet, level):
    # Decompose to get the wavelet coefficients
    coeff = pywt.wavedec(data, wavelet, mode="per", level=level)

    # Threshold for each detail coefficient
    sigma = (1/0.6745) * mad(coeff[-level])
    uthresh = sigma * np.sqrt(2*np.log(len(data)))
    coeff[1:] = (pywt.threshold(data=i, value=uthresh, mode='soft', substitute=0) for i in coeff[1:])
    
    # Reconstruct the signal using the thresholded coefficients
    return pywt.waverec(coeff, wavelet, mode='per')

# Median Absolute Deviation: a robust measure of variability
def mad(data):
    return np.median(np.abs(data - np.median(data)))

# Perform denoising
level = 4
eog_data_dn_bior3 = wavelet_denoise(eog_data, 'bior3.3', level=level)

from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D

def wavelet_denoise_getORGc(data, wavelet, level):
    # Decompose to get the wavelet coefficients
    coeff = pywt.wavedec(data, wavelet, mode="per", level=level)
    return coeff

def wavelet_denoise_getDENc(data, wavelet, level):
    # Decompose to get the wavelet coefficients
    coeff = pywt.wavedec(data, wavelet, mode="per", level=level)
    # Threshold for each detail coefficient
    sigma = (1/0.6745) * mad(coeff[-level])
    uthresh = sigma * np.sqrt(2*np.log(len(data)))
    coeff[1:] = (pywt.threshold(data=i, value=uthresh*0.1, mode='soft', substitute=0) for i in coeff[1:])
    return coeff

# Median Absolute Deviation: a robust measure of variability
def mad(data):
    return np.median(np.abs(data - np.median(data)))

# Get coefficients for visualization and slice them
max_length = 50  # Maximum length to keep from each coefficient array
level=4

coeffs=wavelet_denoise_getORGc(eog_data, 'bior3.3', level=level)
coeffs_dn=wavelet_denoise_getDENc(eog_data, 'bior3.3', level=level)

coeffs = [c[:max_length] for c in coeffs]
coeffs_dn = [c[:max_length] for c in coeffs_dn]

# Setting up the 3D plot
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20, 12))
ax1 = fig.add_subplot(121, projection='3d')
ax2 = fig.add_subplot(122, projection='3d')

# Helper function to plot coefficients in 3D
def plot_coeffs(ax, coeffs, title):
    for i, coeff in enumerate(coeffs):
        xs = np.arange(len(coeff))
        ys = np.ones_like(xs) * i
        zs = np.abs(coeff)
        ax.bar(xs, zs, zs=ys, zdir='y', alpha=0.8, width=1)
    ax.set_xlabel('Sample Index')
    ax.set_ylabel('Decomposition Level')
    ax.set_zlabel('Coefficient Value')
    ax.set_title(title)

# Plot original and denoised signal coefficients
plot_coeffs(ax1, coeffs[1:], 'Original Signal Coefficients')
plot_coeffs(ax2, coeffs_dn[1:], 'Denoised Signal Coefficients')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
